To provide a detailed breakdown of the information in the Professional Services Contract form you provided, I have extracted the relevant information and structured it into a JSON file. Here is the structured breakdown:

```json
{
  "Contract_Details": {
    "Contract_Number": "00000000000000000000000004948",
    "Parties": {
      "State": "Indiana Department of Financial Institutions",
      "Contractor": "MARK STEPHENS"
    },
    "Duties_of_Contractor": {
      "Summary": "The Contractor shall provide the following services relative to this Contract.",
      "Details": [
        "The contractor can perform any and all assigned duties related to State Safety & Soundness Examinations of state-chartered financial institutions, including the role of Examiner-In-Charge (EIC), but duties will primarily focus in the credit union and bank divisions.",
        "Covered duties may involve analysis of any area under examination including, but not limited to, evaluation of Capital, Asset Quality, Management, Earnings, Liquidity, and Interest Rate Risk. Contractor may serve as Asset Manager on examinations as assigned by the EIC.",
        "Contractor may evaluate Operational, Liquidity, Market, Reputational, Legal and Strategic Risks of the financial institution that is being examined.",
        "Contractor may evaluate the adequacy of the financial institution's internal controls, policies, practices, and management information systems.",
        "Contractor may be required to train junior examiners as needed; documenting results as required by Department procedures.",
        "Contractor will be assigned to the Depository Division, and will be assigned to assist on Safety and Soundness examinations of any financial institution in the State of Indiana. This may require contractor to work in both banks and credit unions, depending on Department need. This includes financial institutions of any size and complexity and at any geographic location within the State.",
        "Contractor may be assigned to participate in conversion and/or merger-acquisition related reviews and examinations. In rare instances, these may necessitate the Contractor travel outside the State of Indiana in order to participate on them.",
        "The work product of the Contractor will be submitted to the EIC of the Safety and Soundness examination, and will be included in the Report of Examination as deemed appropriate by the EIC.",
        "Contractor will follow all DFI established examination and non-examination related policies and procedures.",
        "Contractor will report to an assigned Field Manager."
      ]
    },
    "Consideration": {
      "Payment_Rate": "$43.00 per hour",
      "Total_Remuneration": "Shall not exceed $78,000.00",
      "Travel_Expenditures": [
        "Reimbursed at the current rate paid by the State and in accordance with the State Travel Policies and Procedures ... including mileage, hotel, per diem, and parking.",
        "Out-of-state travel requests must be reviewed by the State for availability of funds and for appropriateness per Circular guidelines."
      ],
      "Additional_Provision": [
        "Contractor will be provided with a State of Indiana computer to carry out duties.",
        "State of Indiana computer is for DFI work only, and it not to be used for personal use."
      ]
    },
    "Term": {
      "Effective_Period": "One year",
      "Commencement_Date": "March 23, 2020",
      "End_Date": "March 22, 2021"
    },
    "Access_to_Records": {
      "Summary": "The Contractor and its subcontractors, if any, shall maintain all books, documents, papers, accounting records, and other evidence pertaining to all costs incurred under this Contract.",
      "Details": [
        "They shall make such materials available at their respective offices at all reasonable times during this Contract, and for three (3) years from the date of final payment under this Contract, for inspection by the State or by any other authorized representative of state government.",
        "Copying of records shall be permitted at the State's expense."
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

This JSON file captures the contract number, the parties involved, the duties of the contractor, the considerations, the term of the contract, and the access to records provision specified in the document. The structured format allows for easy understanding and handling of the contract details.
